{
  "name": "Chewiest Protein Brownies",
  "deriveFromRecipe": "Fudgy Protein Brownies",
  "description": "Pushed all the way to chew — derived from the Fudgy base: neutral oil instead of butter (no baking chocolate), the most brown sugar, more flour with ~10-15 extra fold strokes to develop a little gluten, egg-white-forward, no cornstarch. Cocoa + espresso are bloomed in a splash of warm skim milk. 1/4 cup granulated Splenda, baked at 325F for ~18 min and pulled at only a faint wobble. Lands at 12.4 cal per g protein — the leanest of the three. Computed ~621 cal / 50 g protein per batch of 9; ~69 cal, 5.6P, 7.9C, 2.2F per square. Source: user.",
